WEBVTT

00:35.448 --> 00:37.619
[ Man Narrating ]
You're entering the vicinity

00:37.689 --> 00:39.655
of an area adjacent
to a location.

00:39.723 --> 00:42.310
The kind of place where
there might be a monster

00:42.378 --> 00:44.033
or some kind of weird mirror.

00:44.103 --> 00:45.310
These are just examples.

00:45.378 --> 00:47.723
It could also
be something much better.

00:47.792 --> 00:50.310
Prepare to enter...

00:58.412 --> 01:03.171
As per your request, please find
enclosed the last man on earth.

01:04.551 --> 01:06.585
Finally... solitude.

01:06.655 --> 01:10.275
I can read books
for all eternity.

01:11.240 --> 01:12.793
It's not fair.

01:12.861 --> 01:14.655
It's not fair!

01:14.724 --> 01:17.137
Wait. My eyes aren't that bad.

01:17.206 --> 01:20.620
I can still read
the large-print books.

01:20.688 --> 01:22.137
[ Screams ]

01:22.206 --> 01:23.412
It's not f--

01:23.481 --> 01:26.137
Well, lucky I know
how to read Braille.

01:26.206 --> 01:29.412
[ Screams ]

01:29.481 --> 01:31.412
Hey, look at that weird mirror.

01:31.481 --> 01:34.378
[ Shuddering ]CURSED BY
HIS OWN HUBRIS.

01:34.448 --> 01:37.275
THERE'S A POLITICAL DEBATE ON.
QUICK, CHANGE THE CHANNEL.

01:37.343 --> 01:40.723
HEY, THAT'S WHAT FRY SAID
WHEN WE TURNED ONTHE DEBATE.

01:40.793 --> 01:44.378
[ Announcer ]
C-SPAN9 presents
The Thrill of Politics.

01:44.448 --> 01:45.412
[ Snoring ]

01:45.481 --> 01:47.171
[ Sighs ]

01:48.758 --> 01:50.067
WHA--
HUH?

01:50.137 --> 01:52.137
LOOK, I KNOW THERE
ARE NO CAR CHASES,

01:52.206 --> 01:53.620
BUT THIS IS IMPORTANT.

01:53.688 --> 01:56.310
ONE OF THESE TWO MEN WILL
BECOME PRESIDENT OF THE WORLD.

01:56.378 --> 01:58.688
WHAT DO WE CARE?
WE LIVE IN THE UNITED STATES.

01:58.758 --> 02:01.034
THE UNITED STATES
IS PART OF THE WORLD.

02:01.102 --> 02:03.275
WOW, I HAVEBEEN
GONE A LONG TIME.

02:03.343 --> 02:05.310
It's time someone
had the courage

02:05.379 --> 02:06.655
to stand up and say

02:06.724 --> 02:09.688
I'm against those things
that everybody hates!

02:09.758 --> 02:11.723
Now, I respect my opponent.

02:11.793 --> 02:13.378
I think he's a good man.

02:13.448 --> 02:17.550
But, quite frankly, I agree
with everything he just said!

02:17.620 --> 02:21.137
THESE ARE THE CANDIDATES?
THEY SOUND LIKE CLONES.

02:21.205 --> 02:23.481
WAIT A MINUTE.
THEY ARECLONES!

02:23.550 --> 02:25.758
DON'T LET THEIR
IDENTICAL DNA FOOL YOU.

02:25.826 --> 02:27.655
THEY DIFFER ON
SOME KEY ISSUES.

02:27.723 --> 02:31.240
I say your three-cent
titanium tax goes too far.

02:31.310 --> 02:34.103
And I say your
three-cent titanium tax

02:34.171 --> 02:36.067
doesn't go
too far enough.

02:36.137 --> 02:39.033
IF I WERE REGISTERED TO VOTE,
I'D SEND THESE CLOWNS A MESSAGE

02:39.103 --> 02:42.067
BY STAYING HOME ON ELECTION DAY
AND DRESSING UP LIKE A CLOWN!

02:42.137 --> 02:43.275
YOU'RE NOT REGISTERED?!

02:43.343 --> 02:45.067
NOPE. NOT VACCINATED, EITHER.

02:45.137 --> 02:48.275
BESIDES, IT'S NOT LIKE ONE VOTE
EVER MADE A DIFFERENCE.

02:48.343 --> 02:49.586
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

02:49.655 --> 02:52.343
THE FIRST ROBOT PRESIDENT
WON BY EXACTLY ONE VOTE.

02:52.413 --> 02:54.586
AH, YES! JOHN QUINCY
ADDING MACHINE.

02:54.655 --> 02:56.620
HE STRUCK A CHORD
WITH THE VOTERS

02:56.688 --> 02:59.448
WHEN HE PLEDGED NOT TO
GO ON A KILLING SPREE.

02:59.516 --> 03:01.033
BUT, LIKE MOST
POLITICIANS,

03:01.103 --> 03:03.620
HE PROMISED MORE
THAN HE COULD DELIVER.

03:03.688 --> 03:06.171
THE POINT IS, ONE VOTE  CANMAKE A DIFFERENCE.

03:06.240 --> 03:07.516
AND EVEN THOUGH IT WON'T

03:07.586 --> 03:09.655
I'M STILL TAKING YOU
TO GET REGISTERED.

03:09.723 --> 03:12.103
YES, THAT'S
A CAPITAL IDEA.

03:12.171 --> 03:14.137
LET'S ALL
GO REGISTER.

03:14.205 --> 03:16.826
PROFESSOR, WHEN DID YOU BECOME
SO OBSESSED WITH VOTING?

03:16.896 --> 03:19.413
THE VERY INSTANT
I BECAME OLD.

03:23.793 --> 03:24.861
MMM!

03:26.413 --> 03:27.620
MMM!

03:27.688 --> 03:29.068
THE PROBLEM
WITH BOTH PARTIES

03:29.137 --> 03:31.516
IS THAT THEY ALWAYS
WANT TO GIVE YOUR TAX DOLLARS

03:31.586 --> 03:32.688
TO THE LESS FORTUNATE.

03:32.758 --> 03:34.793
THE LESS FORTUNATE
GET ALL THE BREAKS.

03:34.861 --> 03:38.137
YOU KNOW, FRY, YOU COULD
JOIN A THIRD PARTY, MAYBE.

03:38.206 --> 03:40.861
ONLY WEIRDOS AND MUTANTS
JOIN THIRD PARTIES.

03:40.930 --> 03:44.620
REALLY? I BETTER KEEP AN EYE OUT
AT THE NEXT MEETING.

03:44.688 --> 03:46.343
WHAT PARTY DO YOU
BELONG TO, BENDER?

03:46.413 --> 03:47.930
EH, I'M NOT ALLOWED TO VOTE.

03:48.000 --> 03:49.033
'CAUSE YOU'RE A ROBOT?

03:49.103 --> 03:50.758
NO. CONVICTED FELON.

03:57.930 --> 03:59.655
WE FAVOR UNREASONABLY
HUGE SUBSIDIES

03:59.723 --> 04:02.171
TO THE BRAIN
SLUG PLANET.

04:02.241 --> 04:04.620
OKAY, BUT WHAT ARE
THE BRAIN SLUGS
WHO CONTROL YOU

04:04.688 --> 04:06.205
GOING TO DO
FOR THE WORKING MAN?

04:06.275 --> 04:08.068
ATTACH BRAIN SLUGS TO THEM.

04:08.137 --> 04:10.068
SURE, YOU SAY THAT NOW.

04:12.137 --> 04:13.481
SO IS IT TRUE
YOU CAN MAKE

04:13.550 --> 04:15.793
ALL KINDS OF SHIRTS
AND ROPES OUT OF HEMP?

04:15.861 --> 04:17.723
DAVE'S NOT HERE, MAN.

04:17.793 --> 04:20.240
I ALSO HEARD HEMP
MAKES GREAT SHAMPOO.

04:20.310 --> 04:21.862
IT DOES? NO WAY!

04:21.930 --> 04:24.379
I GOT TO CHECK OUT
THIS BROCHURE.

04:24.447 --> 04:25.757
[ Gulping ]

04:28.137 --> 04:30.206
SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
TO PROTECT

04:30.274 --> 04:33.379
MY CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHT
TO BEAR DOOMSDAY DEVICES?

04:33.447 --> 04:35.550
WELL, FIRST OFF,
WE'RE GOING TO GET RID

04:35.620 --> 04:38.723
OF THAT THREE-DAY WAITING
PERIOD FOR MAD SCIENTISTS.

04:38.793 --> 04:40.274
DAMN STRAIGHT!

04:40.343 --> 04:43.310
TODAY, THE MAD SCIENTIST
CAN'T GET A DOOMSDAY DEVICE.

04:43.379 --> 04:45.447
TOMORROW, IT'S
THE MAD GRAD STUDENT!

04:45.516 --> 04:47.000
WHERE WILL IT END?

04:47.067 --> 04:48.516
AMEN, BROTHER!

04:48.586 --> 04:51.067
I DON'T GO ANYWHERE
WITHOUT MY MUTATED ANTHRAX--

04:51.137 --> 04:52.723
FOR DUCK HUNTIN'.

04:52.793 --> 04:55.103
SURE,
HUMANS ARE CUTE

04:55.172 --> 04:57.206
BUT HOW ELSE ARE WE SUPPOSED
TO TEST COSMETICS?

04:57.274 --> 04:59.206
I CONCUR.

04:59.274 --> 05:03.757
NOW HERE'S A PARTY
I CAN GET EXCITED ABOUT.
SIGN ME UP.

05:03.826 --> 05:05.930
SORRY, NOT WITH
THAT ATTITUDE.

05:06.000 --> 05:07.413
OKAY, THEN SCREW IT.

05:07.482 --> 05:09.103
WELCOME ABOARD,
BROTHER!

05:09.172 --> 05:11.103
- ALL RIGHT!
- YOU'RE OUT.

05:12.723 --> 05:15.206
[ Fry ]
THAT WAS PRETTY COOL.

05:15.274 --> 05:18.000
I THINK I'M ACTUALLY STARTING
TO GET INTERESTED IN POLITICS.

05:18.067 --> 05:20.757
- [ Beeping ]
- [ Theme Music Plays ]

05:20.826 --> 05:24.689
[ Both Snoring ]

05:24.757 --> 05:26.757
And so, with two weeks
left in the campaign,

05:26.826 --> 05:28.310
the question on
everyone's mind

05:28.379 --> 05:30.310
is who will be

05:30.379 --> 05:31.862
the next President
of Earth--

05:31.930 --> 05:35.379
Jack Johnson, or bitter
rival John Jackson?

05:35.447 --> 05:38.379
Two terrific candidates,
huh, Morbo?

05:38.447 --> 05:42.000
All humans are vermin
in the eyes of Morbo.

05:42.067 --> 05:44.654
[ Laughing ]

05:44.723 --> 05:46.103
In other local news

05:46.172 --> 05:49.206
disaster struck on
Saturn's moon of
Titan today

05:49.274 --> 05:51.206
when a titanium
mine collapsed

05:51.274 --> 05:53.137
trapping 1,000
robot workers.

05:53.206 --> 05:55.481
WHAT? LORD HAVE MERCY!

05:55.550 --> 05:57.206
Unless something is done quickly

05:57.274 --> 06:00.206
the trapped robots
will be dead within 300 years.

06:00.274 --> 06:03.343
Sir, what rescue operations
are planned?

06:03.413 --> 06:06.343
The plan is, basically,
to pave over the area

06:06.413 --> 06:08.137
and get on with our lives.

06:08.206 --> 06:09.240
[ Horrified Gasp ]

06:09.310 --> 06:10.826
News of the mine's closing

06:10.896 --> 06:12.930
sent titanium prices
skyrocketing.

06:13.000 --> 06:14.067
ALL RIGHT! I'M RICH!

06:14.137 --> 06:15.310
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

06:15.379 --> 06:17.240
MY BODY'S 40% TITANIUM.

06:17.310 --> 06:21.413
I'M FINALLY RICHER THAN
THOSE SNOOTY A.T.M. MACHINES.

06:21.481 --> 06:22.930
TOO BAD YOU CAN'T SPEND IT.

06:23.000 --> 06:25.654
- OH, CAN'T I?
- NO.

06:25.723 --> 06:27.654
WATCH ME, POOR MAN.

06:27.723 --> 06:30.481
[ Shopkeeper ]
PLEASURE DOIN' BUSINESS
WITH YOU.

06:30.550 --> 06:32.206
[ Bender Laughing ]

06:32.274 --> 06:33.862
GAME'S OVER, LOSERS!

06:33.930 --> 06:35.654
I HAVE ALLTHE MONEY.

06:35.723 --> 06:40.137
COMPARE YOUR LIVES TO MINE
AND THEN KILL YOURSELVES.

06:40.206 --> 06:41.586
[ Sniffing ]

06:41.654 --> 06:43.620
HEY, GET AWAY! SHOO!

06:43.689 --> 06:46.447
I'LL GIVE YOU $5.00
TO NOT DO WHAT YOU'RE
THINKING ABOUT DOING.

06:48.550 --> 06:52.862
[ Bender Chuckles ]
YOU JUST LOST $5.00.

06:57.586 --> 06:59.103
HEY, BUDDY! LITTLE HELP?

06:59.172 --> 07:00.172
[ Grunting ]

07:00.240 --> 07:01.826
THANK YOU!

07:01.896 --> 07:03.103
[ All Gasping ]

07:05.240 --> 07:06.723
HELLO, PEASANTS.

07:06.793 --> 07:08.723
BENDER!
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

07:08.793 --> 07:10.757
YOU LOOK DIFFERENT.
DID YOU GET A HAIRCUT?

07:10.826 --> 07:12.206
NO! I SOLD MY BODY.

07:12.274 --> 07:13.689
[ Spitting ]

07:13.757 --> 07:14.826
SOLD YOUR BODY?!

07:14.896 --> 07:17.033
OH, BENDER,
I'VE BEEN DOWN THAT ROAD.

07:17.103 --> 07:20.103
I KNOW IT'S GLAMOROUS
AND THE PARTIES ARE GREAT,

07:20.172 --> 07:23.379
BUT YOU'LL END UP SPENDING
EVERY DOLLAR YOU MAKE

07:23.447 --> 07:25.516
ON JEWELRY
AND SKINTIGHT PANTS.

07:25.586 --> 07:26.689
THIS IS CRAZY, BENDER.

07:26.757 --> 07:28.550
HOW ARE YOU GOING TO LIVE
WITHOUT A BODY?

07:28.620 --> 07:29.689
[ Raspberry ]

07:29.757 --> 07:31.793
BODIES ARE FOR HOOKERS
AND FAT PEOPLE.

07:31.862 --> 07:35.103
ALL I NEED IS A WAD
OF CASH WITH A HEAD
WRAPPED AROUND IT.

07:35.172 --> 07:37.481
WELL, AT LEAST NOW
YOU CAN PAY OFF YOUR LOAN SHARK.

07:37.550 --> 07:39.689
YEAH, RIGHT,
WHAT'S HE GOING TO DO,
BREAK MY LEGS?

07:39.757 --> 07:41.000
[ Laughing ]

07:42.550 --> 07:44.620
AH, THIS IS THE LIFE!

07:44.689 --> 07:47.033
ANOTHER MARTINI, PLEASE!

07:49.516 --> 07:52.550
SHAKEN, NOT STIRRED.

07:52.620 --> 07:55.826
[ Bouncing ]
OH, YEAH!

07:58.550 --> 08:00.033
PUT IT ALL ON BLACK.

08:00.103 --> 08:01.964
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA!

08:02.033 --> 08:04.000
[ Grunting ]

08:07.240 --> 08:09.103
21 RED.

08:09.172 --> 08:10.240
[ Grunts ]

08:10.310 --> 08:12.240
I BEG YOUR PARDON--
33 BLACK.

08:12.310 --> 08:13.723
YES!

08:13.793 --> 08:15.137
THE RICH GET RICHER.

08:22.723 --> 08:24.689
[ Grunting ]

08:26.447 --> 08:28.964
STRIKE!
IN YOUR FACE, LEELA!

08:29.033 --> 08:32.793
[ Laughing ]

08:32.861 --> 08:34.274
OW!

08:36.000 --> 08:38.136
[ Screeching ]

08:40.000 --> 08:42.102
[ Screaming ] [ Screaming ]

08:45.033 --> 08:46.136
[ Muttering ]

08:46.206 --> 08:47.274
[ Grunting ]

08:47.344 --> 08:48.620
TIMBER!

08:50.826 --> 08:53.136
HEY, BENDER, CAN I TAKE
A RIDE IN YOUR CAR?

08:53.206 --> 08:54.861
MAYBE IF YOU CLEAN UP FIRST.

08:54.931 --> 08:56.965
IT LOOKS LIKE YOUR NECK
STEPPED IN SOMETHING.

08:57.033 --> 08:58.309
OH, I'M SORRY.

08:58.379 --> 09:01.481
THAT'S JUST YOUR BODY.

09:01.551 --> 09:03.000
[ Laughing ]

09:03.067 --> 09:05.793
HEY, YOU LOOK ME
IN THE SHINS AND SAY THAT.

09:05.861 --> 09:08.447
HEY, I'VE HAD IT
UP TO HERE WITH THIS PLACE.

09:08.517 --> 09:10.000
I'M OFF
TO THE HEAD MUSEUM

09:10.067 --> 09:12.274
TO HANG OUT
WITH CLASSY HEADS LIKE ME

09:12.344 --> 09:14.344
WHO APPRECIATE
THE FINER THINGS:

09:14.413 --> 09:17.102
POETRY, PHILOSOPHY, HATS.

09:17.172 --> 09:19.517
SO LONG,
COFFIN-STUFFERS!

09:19.586 --> 09:21.965
[ Engine Revving ]

09:22.033 --> 09:23.654
[ Tires Squealing ]

09:23.724 --> 09:25.379
[ Head Muttering ]

09:27.274 --> 09:30.379
COULD ONE OF YOU COFFIN-STUFFERS
PLEASE CARRY ME?

09:40.447 --> 09:41.895
NOW, WHICH GROUP OF HEADS

09:41.965 --> 09:44.517
IS GOOD ENOUGH FOR ME
TO HANG OUT WITH?

09:44.586 --> 09:45.931
WHAT DO YOU THINK, FRY?

09:46.000 --> 09:47.000
FRY?

09:47.067 --> 09:48.136
MMM.

09:48.206 --> 09:49.413
HI.

09:49.481 --> 09:50.481
I'M CLAUDIA
SCHIFFER'S HEAD.

09:50.551 --> 09:51.724
I RECOGNIZE YOU.

09:51.793 --> 09:53.895
DIDN'T YOU USE TO HAVE
A BODY OF SOME SORT?

09:53.965 --> 09:56.102
YEAH, BUT IT WAS
HOLDING ME BACK.

09:56.172 --> 09:57.895
YOU KNOW, I JUST
DID THE COVER

09:57.965 --> 10:00.344
OF THE SPORTS
ILLUSTRATED
SWIM CAP ISSUE.

10:00.413 --> 10:01.654
[ Purring ]

10:01.724 --> 10:03.206
WELL,
YOU'RE LOOKING GREAT.

10:03.274 --> 10:06.240
THANKS. I WOULDN'T
MIND LOSING A
FEW POUNDS, THOUGH.

10:06.309 --> 10:07.447
COULDN'T HURT.

10:09.517 --> 10:12.861
AH, U.S. PRESIDENTS!

10:12.931 --> 10:15.724
STURDY SHELVES,
GOOD SECURITY...

10:16.895 --> 10:18.724
THIS PLACE HAS CLASS.

10:18.793 --> 10:20.033
[ Clinton ]
HEY, SUGAR COOKIE!

10:20.102 --> 10:21.206
YOU KNOW, LEGALLY

10:21.274 --> 10:23.758
NOTHING I CAN DO
COUNTS AS SEX ANYMORE.

10:23.826 --> 10:25.758
I APOLOGIZE
FOR HIS RUDENESS, MA'AM.

10:25.826 --> 10:28.274
HE GETS THIS WAY
AROUND MEATY-LOOKING WOMEN.

10:28.344 --> 10:29.413
HEY, I REMEMBER YOU.

10:29.481 --> 10:31.620
I WAS GOING TO VOTE
FOR YOU ONE TIME.

10:31.688 --> 10:33.000
BUT VOTING ISN'T COOL

10:33.067 --> 10:35.551
SO I STAYED HOME ALONE
AND GOT TRASHED ON LISTERINE.

10:35.620 --> 10:37.172
FRANKLY, I'VE NEVER
FELT VOTING

10:37.240 --> 10:39.309
TO BE ALL THAT ESSENTIAL
TO THE PROCESS.

10:39.379 --> 10:41.793
NO KIDDING, FORD.

10:41.861 --> 10:43.688
SO THEN
THE HOOKER-BOT SAYS

10:43.758 --> 10:45.826
"THAT'S NOT
MY EXPANSION SLOT."

10:45.895 --> 10:47.172
AND MY FRIEND SAYS

10:47.240 --> 10:50.102
"THAT'S NOT MY GOLD-PLATED
25-PIN CONNECTOR."

10:50.172 --> 10:51.413
[ Laughing ]

10:51.481 --> 10:52.895
[ Laughing ]

10:52.965 --> 10:54.000
OH, BENDER.

10:54.067 --> 10:56.895
THOU ROBOTS REALLY
CRACKETH ME UP.

10:56.965 --> 10:58.654
YOU KNOW,
I LIKE IT HERE.

10:58.724 --> 11:00.724
WHAT'S THE RENT
ON ONE OF THESE JARS?

11:00.793 --> 11:02.895
SORRY, BENDER,
BUT WE CAN'T ALLOW

11:02.965 --> 11:05.309
EVERY TOM, DICK
AND HARRY TO MOVE IN.

11:05.379 --> 11:07.861
NO OFFENSE JEFFERSON,
NIXON AND TRUMAN.

11:07.931 --> 11:09.447
MAYBE MR. BENDER CAN GET A SPOT

11:09.517 --> 11:11.481
IN THE CLOSET
OF PRESIDENTIAL LOSERS.

11:11.551 --> 11:13.413
BOB DOLE NEEDS COMPANY.

11:13.481 --> 11:15.861
LAROUCHE WON'T STOP
WITH THE KNOCK-KNOCK JOKES.

11:15.931 --> 11:16.931
PASS.

11:17.000 --> 11:18.033
SO TELLETH, BENDER--

11:18.102 --> 11:19.758
WHAT HATH HAPPENED
TO YOUR BODY?

11:19.826 --> 11:20.895
I HOCKED IT.

11:20.965 --> 11:22.688
HOCKED IT?
WHY WOULDST
THOU DO THAT?

11:22.758 --> 11:24.551
SAME REASON
YOU HOCKED YOUR TEETH.

11:24.620 --> 11:26.965
AH, BOOZE MONEY.

11:27.033 --> 11:28.688
I REMEMBER
MY BODY.

11:28.758 --> 11:32.724
FLABBY, PASTY-SKINNED,
RIDDLED WITH PHLEBITIS.

11:32.793 --> 11:34.344
A GOOD REPUBLICAN BODY.

11:34.413 --> 11:36.067
GOD, I LOVED IT.

11:36.136 --> 11:37.379
I HEAR THAT.

11:37.447 --> 11:39.586
I SPENT MOST
OF MY TEEN YEARS
LOVING MY BODY.

11:39.654 --> 11:41.136
COURSE, IT
WAS TOUGH LOVE--

11:41.206 --> 11:42.274
[ Grunting ]

11:42.344 --> 11:45.000
FRY, HE OPENED UP
RELATIONS WITH CHINA.

11:45.067 --> 11:47.000
HE DOESN'T WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT YOUR DING-DONG.

11:47.067 --> 11:49.344
SO, NIXON,
EVEN IF YOU MISS YOUR BODY

11:49.413 --> 11:51.413
BEING A HEAD'S GREAT,
TOO, RIGHT?

11:51.481 --> 11:52.517
NO, SON.

11:52.586 --> 11:54.861
IT'S A SAD
AND LONELY LIFE.

11:54.931 --> 11:56.931
OH, GREAT.
NOW YOU TELL ME.

11:57.000 --> 11:58.379
THAT'S MY STYLE.

11:58.447 --> 12:00.620
I LIKE TO KICK 'EM
WHEN THEY'RE DOWN.

12:04.620 --> 12:06.861
[ Muttering ]

12:08.758 --> 12:11.793
[ Groaning ] ONE, ZERO, UH--

12:11.861 --> 12:14.895
ONE, ONE, ZERO, ZERO, ONE--

12:14.965 --> 12:16.102
[ Screaming ]

12:16.172 --> 12:17.654
BENDER, WHAT IS IT?

12:17.724 --> 12:19.586
WHOA, WHAT
AN AWFUL DREAM.

12:19.654 --> 12:21.620
ONES AND ZEROS
EVERYWHERE.

12:21.688 --> 12:22.758
[ Shuddering ]

12:22.826 --> 12:24.861
AND I THOUGHT
I SAW A TWO.

12:24.931 --> 12:26.447
IT WAS JUST A DREAM,
BENDER.

12:26.517 --> 12:28.033
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS TWO.

12:28.102 --> 12:30.000
I KNOW WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

12:30.067 --> 12:33.344
MY BODY LOVED ME
AND I TURNED ITS BACK ON IT.

12:33.413 --> 12:37.379
WELL, OLD FRIEND, TIE
A YELLOW RIBBON 'ROUND YOUR NECK

12:37.447 --> 12:39.344
'CAUSE I'M A-COMIN' HOME.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.033
YOU SOLD MY BODY?!
TO WHO?!

12:43.102 --> 12:44.654
I CAN'T REVEAL
THAT INFORMATION

12:44.724 --> 12:46.067
BUT YOU LOOK LIKE
A NICE ROBOT.

12:46.136 --> 12:48.586
TELL YOU WHAT--
I'LL GIVE YOU 50
BUCKS FOR THE KID.

12:48.654 --> 12:51.102
HEY, MY CLOTHES
ARE WORTH 50 BUCKS.

12:51.172 --> 12:52.136
DEAL.

12:52.206 --> 12:54.344
[ Moaning ]

12:54.413 --> 12:57.000
HOW COULD I LET THIS HAPPEN?

12:57.067 --> 13:00.274
I CAN'T GO THROUGH
THE REST OF MY LIFE LIKE THIS.

13:00.344 --> 13:02.654
DON'T YOU HAVE
A SELF-DESTRUCT BUTTON?

13:02.724 --> 13:06.344
YEAH...
BUT IT'S ON MY BODY.

13:06.413 --> 13:08.895
WHAT AM I GOING TO DO?

13:08.965 --> 13:10.102
[ Sobbing ]

13:11.447 --> 13:15.172
UH, I CAN'T STAND
TO SEE A ROBOT CRY.

13:15.240 --> 13:16.620
LET'S WATCH TV.

13:16.688 --> 13:18.895
And so, ladies and gentlemen

13:18.965 --> 13:21.826
I'm throwing my head
into the ring.

13:21.895 --> 13:26.344
I'm announcing my candidacy
for the Presidency of Earth.

13:26.413 --> 13:27.447
[ Reporters Shouting ]

13:27.517 --> 13:28.758
SCOOP CHANG,
BEIJING BUGLE.

13:28.826 --> 13:30.586
SIR, THE CONSTITUTION
CLEARLY STATES

13:30.654 --> 13:33.481
THAT NOBODY CAN BE ELECTED
PRESIDENT MORE THAN TWICE.

13:33.551 --> 13:36.067
THAT'S RIGHT... NO BODY.

13:36.136 --> 13:39.965
BUT AS YOU CAN PLAINLY SEE,
I'VE GOT A SHINY NEW BODY.

13:40.033 --> 13:43.206
[ Humming Melody ]

13:43.274 --> 13:44.379
[ Gasping ]

13:44.447 --> 13:46.136
BENDER, HE'S GOT
YOUR BODY!

13:46.206 --> 13:48.965
THAT DIRTY,
DOUBLE-CROSSING BASTARD!

13:49.033 --> 13:51.586
HOW DARE HE RUN OFF
WITH RICHARD NIXON.

13:54.551 --> 13:57.413
NIXON MUST HAVE BOUGHT YOUR BODY
FROM THE PAWNSHOP.

13:57.481 --> 13:59.102
YEAH, AND THAT
ELECTRIC GUITAR.

13:59.172 --> 14:04.586
♪ Remember
what the dormouse said ♪

14:06.309 --> 14:08.724
♪ Feed your head... ♪

14:08.793 --> 14:12.517
I'm meeting you halfway,
you stupid hippies.

14:12.586 --> 14:15.136
[ Cheering ]

14:15.206 --> 14:17.240
I am not a crook's head.

14:17.309 --> 14:19.724
YEAH, YOU ARE.
YOU STOLE MY BODY!

14:19.793 --> 14:22.586
FRY, LEELA,
YOU GOT TO HELP ME.

14:22.654 --> 14:24.793
ORDINARILY, I'D SAY
NO AND LECTURE YOU

14:24.861 --> 14:27.826
ON HOW THIS IS YOUR
OWN FAULT FOR BEING
SUCH AN IDIOT.

14:27.895 --> 14:30.136
BUT WHEN A ROBOTIC
NIXON IS ON THE LOOSE,

14:30.206 --> 14:32.067
WE HAVE A DUTY
TO TAKE ACTION.

14:32.136 --> 14:33.481
IDIOT.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.965
[ Audience Murmuring ]

14:47.033 --> 14:49.895
MORBO WILL NOW INTRODUCE
TONIGHT'S CANDIDATES.

14:49.965 --> 14:51.826
PUNY HUMAN NUMBER ONE,

14:51.895 --> 14:54.206
PUNY HUMAN NUMBER TWO,

14:54.274 --> 14:57.000
AND MORBO'S
GOOD FRIEND,
RICHARD NIXON.

14:57.067 --> 14:59.895
HELLO, MORBO.
HOW'S THE FAMILY?

14:59.965 --> 15:02.172
BELLIGERENT AND NUMEROUS.

15:02.240 --> 15:03.413
GOOD MAN.

15:03.481 --> 15:05.895
NIXON'S PRO-WAR
AND PRO-FAMILY.

15:05.965 --> 15:07.861
[ Applause ]

15:10.033 --> 15:14.033
GREAT. FIRST HE STEALS MY BODY,
NOW HE'S TOUCHING MY STUFF.

15:14.102 --> 15:16.965
COME ON. WE'VE GOT
TO FIND SOME WAY
TO TALK TO HIM.

15:19.000 --> 15:21.931
MORBO DEMANDS AN ANSWER
TO THE FOLLOWING QUESTION:

15:22.000 --> 15:26.067
"IF YOU SAW DELICIOUS CANDY
IN THE HANDS OF A SMALL CHILD

15:26.136 --> 15:28.895
WOULD YOU SEIZE AND CONSUME IT?"

15:28.965 --> 15:30.033
UNTHINKABLE!

15:30.102 --> 15:31.861
I WOULDN'T THINK OF IT!

15:31.931 --> 15:33.447
WHAT ABOUT YOU,
MR. NIXON?

15:33.517 --> 15:36.481
I REMIND YOU, YOU ARE
UNDER A TRUTH-O-SCOPE.

15:36.551 --> 15:38.826
UH, WELL, UH...

15:38.895 --> 15:41.517
THE QUESTION IS-IS VAGUE.

15:41.586 --> 15:43.620
YOU DON'T SAY
WHAT KIND OF CANDY,

15:43.688 --> 15:45.965
UH, WHETHER ANYONE
IS WATCHING...

15:46.033 --> 15:48.724
[ Mumbles, Clears Throat ]

15:48.793 --> 15:52.413
AT ANY RATE, I CERTAINLY
WOULDN'T HARM THE CHILD.

15:52.481 --> 15:54.172
[ Beeping ]

15:57.447 --> 15:59.965
YOU SCORED BIG POINTS
TONIGHT, SIR.

16:00.033 --> 16:03.688
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
THEY ATE ME ALIVE OUT THERE.

16:03.758 --> 16:05.793
YES, BUT YOUR BODY
STAYED ON MESSAGE

16:05.861 --> 16:08.793
AND THAT MESSAGE IS,
"LOOK AT MY SHINY NEW BODY."

16:08.861 --> 16:10.136
THE ROBOTS ATE IT UP.

16:10.206 --> 16:12.688
YOU'VE GOT REAL CHARISMA
FROM THE NECK DOWN.

16:12.758 --> 16:14.413
NIXON WITH CHARISMA.

16:14.481 --> 16:16.102
MY GOD!

16:16.172 --> 16:17.758
I CAN RULE THE UNIVERSE!

16:17.826 --> 16:19.586
[ All Gasping ]

16:19.654 --> 16:22.447
GIVE ME MY BODY BACK,
YOU TWO-BIT THIEF!

16:22.517 --> 16:24.861
NOW, LOOK HERE,
YOU DRUGGED-OUT COMMUNIST,

16:24.931 --> 16:27.724
I PAID FOR THIS BODY
AND I'D NO SOONER RETURN IT

16:27.793 --> 16:30.895
THAN I WOULD MY LITTLE COCKER
SPANIEL DOG, CHECKERS.

16:30.965 --> 16:33.000
- [ Yelps ]
- SHUT UP, DAMN IT!

16:33.067 --> 16:34.274
PLEASE, MR. NIXON

16:34.344 --> 16:36.654
WE'RE APPEALING TO
YOUR SENSE OF DECENCY.

16:36.724 --> 16:38.240
[ Laughing ]

16:38.309 --> 16:40.309
VERY GOOD!

16:41.758 --> 16:45.240
SERIOUSLY, THOUGH, I'M NEVER
GIVING BACK THIS BODY.

16:45.309 --> 16:48.654
NOW, BEAT IT, BEFORE I GET
CAMBODIAN ON YOUR ASSES!

16:52.033 --> 16:54.136
[ Bender Crying ]
IT'S HOPELESS.

16:54.206 --> 16:57.931
WE MIGHT AS WELL TURN IN MY HEAD
FOR THE FIVE-CENT DEPOSIT.

16:58.000 --> 16:59.136
NO WAY.

16:59.206 --> 17:02.000
I'M NOT LETTING MY BEST FRIEND
GET RECYCLED--

17:02.067 --> 17:04.378
NOT FOR FIVE CENTS,
NOT FOR 500 CENTS.

17:04.448 --> 17:05.862
LEELA, I'VE GOT A PLAN.

17:05.931 --> 17:07.240
I'VEGOT A
BETTER PLAN.

17:15.240 --> 17:17.758
[ Whispering ]
WHY WOULD NIXON STAY
AT THE WATERGATE?

17:17.826 --> 17:20.240
THEY GIVE YOU A DISCOUNT
IF YOU'VE BEEN HERE BEFORE.

17:30.034 --> 17:33.000
[ Grunting ]

17:33.067 --> 17:35.413
[ Fry ]
KEEP GOING.
WE'RE RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

17:37.309 --> 17:39.689
WHOA, MAMA. GET
A ROOM, YOU TWO.

17:39.758 --> 17:41.413
[ Man ]
WE'RE IN A ROOM!

17:41.481 --> 17:43.723
WELL, THEN,
LOSE SOME WEIGHT.

17:43.792 --> 17:45.792
[ Grunting ]

17:45.862 --> 17:47.550
[ Man Snoring ]

17:47.619 --> 17:48.689
[ Exhaling Loudly ]

17:48.758 --> 17:50.723
[ Snoring ]

17:50.792 --> 17:55.964
OH, YEAH, YOU WOMEN'S LIBBERS
REALLY KNOW HOW TO PARTY.

17:56.034 --> 17:57.378
PSST, THERE I AM.

17:58.448 --> 18:00.550
[ Squeaking ]

18:00.619 --> 18:02.172
[ Snoring Continuing ]

18:02.240 --> 18:04.034
HEY, BETTY FRIEDAN,

18:04.103 --> 18:07.689
SEND A LITTLE OF
THAT LOTION MY WAY.

18:07.758 --> 18:10.034
OKAY, ALMOST GOT IT.

18:10.103 --> 18:11.309
STEADY...

18:11.378 --> 18:12.619
STEADY...

18:12.689 --> 18:14.378
DON'T PANIC.

18:15.413 --> 18:17.344
OOH.

18:17.413 --> 18:18.619
UH-OH.

18:18.689 --> 18:21.205
[ Groaning And Yelling ]

18:22.586 --> 18:24.067
HUH? WHAT THE--

18:27.275 --> 18:30.448
YOU SHAGGY PEACENIKS
HAVE SOME NERVE.

18:30.517 --> 18:32.000
I'M JUST HERE
FOR WHAT'S MINE.

18:32.067 --> 18:33.586
DON'T MAKE ME KICK YOUR NECK.

18:33.654 --> 18:35.205
BRING IT ON, SOUP CAN.

18:35.275 --> 18:37.481
- [ Growling ]
- [ Gasping ]

18:37.550 --> 18:39.205
[ Both Snarling ]

18:39.275 --> 18:40.758
[ Growling, Snarling
Continuing ]

18:40.826 --> 18:42.586
ALL RIGHT,
BREAK IT UP, YOU TWO.

18:44.413 --> 18:45.448
THAT'S IT!

18:45.517 --> 18:46.862
YOU'RE ALL GOING TO JAIL

18:46.931 --> 18:49.344
AND DON'T EXPECT ME
TO GRANT A PARDON

18:49.413 --> 18:50.792
LIKE THAT SISSY FORD.

18:50.862 --> 18:52.378
YOU'LL NEVER
PARDON ANYBODY

18:52.448 --> 18:55.000
BECAUSE YOU'LL NEVER
GET ELECTED PRESIDENT.

18:55.067 --> 18:58.723
THE VOTERS OF EARTH AREN'T
THE PEA-BRAINED IDIOTS THEY WERE
BACK IN YOUR TIME.

18:58.792 --> 19:00.895
OH, NO?
WELL, LISTEN HERE, MISSY.

19:00.964 --> 19:04.378
COMPUTERS MAY BE TWICE AS FAST
AS THEY WERE IN 1973

19:04.448 --> 19:08.205
BUT YOUR AVERAGE VOTER IS
AS DRUNK AND STUPID AS EVER.

19:08.275 --> 19:10.240
THE ONLY ONE
WHO'S CHANGED IS ME.

19:10.309 --> 19:12.586
I'VE BECOME BITTER
AND, LET'S FACE IT--

19:12.654 --> 19:14.689
CRAZY OVER THE YEARS.

19:14.758 --> 19:16.723
AND ONCE I'M
SWEPT INTO OFFICE,

19:16.792 --> 19:19.826
I'LL SELL OUR CHILDREN'S ORGANS
TO ZOOS FOR MEAT

19:19.895 --> 19:23.964
AND I'LL GO INTO PEOPLE'S HOUSES
AT NIGHT AND WRECK UP THE PLACE.

19:24.034 --> 19:25.619
[ Laughing Villainously ]

19:25.689 --> 19:28.172
WELL, HE LOST MY VOTE.

19:28.240 --> 19:30.550
LIKE ONE VOTE
EVER MADE A DIFFERENCE.

19:30.619 --> 19:32.034
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

19:32.103 --> 19:34.689
I'M GOING TO INCH MYSELF
OVER TO THE PHONE

19:34.758 --> 19:36.000
AND CALL THE POLICE.

19:36.067 --> 19:38.240
[ Grunting ]

19:38.309 --> 19:40.309
NOT SO FAST, NIXON!

19:40.378 --> 19:42.826
ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH... AUDIO TAPE?

19:42.895 --> 19:44.895
[ Tape Rewinding ]

19:44.964 --> 19:47.689
UH-OH, I DON'T LIKE
WHERE THIS IS HEADING.

19:47.758 --> 19:49.964
And I'll go
into people's houses at night

19:50.034 --> 19:51.103
and wreck up the place.

19:51.172 --> 19:53.448
[ Laughing Villainously ]

19:53.517 --> 19:55.689
MY GOD,
I REALLY SOUND LIKE THAT?

19:55.758 --> 19:59.205
I THOUGHT MY VOICE HAD
MORE OF A CLARK GABLE QUALITY.

19:59.275 --> 20:00.517
[ Mechanical Whining ]

20:00.586 --> 20:01.723
THE JIG'S UP, NIXON.

20:01.792 --> 20:03.517
WE'LL TRADE YOU THE TAPE
FOR THE BODY.

20:03.586 --> 20:05.758
OH, EXPLETIVE DELETED.

20:05.826 --> 20:07.517
YOU'VE GOT A DEAL.

20:07.586 --> 20:10.172
HEY, I'VE GOT
ONE LAST THOUGHT.

20:10.240 --> 20:13.136
[ Groaning ]

20:16.826 --> 20:20.275
AH, IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK
IN ONE PIECE AGAIN...

20:20.344 --> 20:23.586
EXCEPT I CAN'T GET THESE
DAMN BUMPER STICKERS OFF.

20:23.654 --> 20:25.550
The sheer drama
of this election

20:25.619 --> 20:27.103
has driven voter turnout

20:27.172 --> 20:30.172
to its highest level in
centuries-- six percent.

20:30.240 --> 20:33.758
Exit polls show evil underdog
Richard Nixon trailing

20:33.826 --> 20:35.758
with an estimated
zero votes.

20:35.826 --> 20:38.034
YES! THE SYSTEM WORKS.

20:38.103 --> 20:39.240
The time is 7:59

20:39.309 --> 20:41.792
and the robot polls
are now opening...

20:41.862 --> 20:43.448
and the robot vote is in.

20:43.517 --> 20:44.862
Nixon has won!

20:44.931 --> 20:46.481
GET OUT OF TOWN!OH, NO!OOH...

20:46.550 --> 20:48.067
WHY WOULD ROBOTS VOTE
FOR NIXON

20:48.136 --> 20:50.205
NOW THAT HE'S JUST A HEAD
IN A JAR?

20:51.862 --> 20:55.895
I GIVE YOU THE NEXT PRESIDENT
OF EARTH!

20:57.136 --> 20:58.378
[ Crashing Thunderously ]

20:58.448 --> 20:59.654
[ Grunts ]

20:59.723 --> 21:01.826
NIXON'S BACK!

21:01.895 --> 21:03.964
[ Cheering ]

21:04.034 --> 21:07.895
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
HE WON BY A SINGLE VOTE.

21:07.964 --> 21:09.378
WELL, IT AIN'T MY FAULT.

21:09.448 --> 21:11.517
I'M A NON-VOTING FELON,
THANK YOU.

21:11.586 --> 21:14.136
WELL, IT'S NOT MY FAULT, EITHER,
'CAUSE I FORGOT TO VOTE.

21:14.205 --> 21:18.034
OH, CRUD, I KNEWTHERE WAS
SOMETHING I MEANT TO DO TODAY.

21:18.103 --> 21:22.448
Morbo congratulates
our gargantuan cyborg president.

21:22.517 --> 21:25.654
May death come quickly
to his enemies.

21:25.723 --> 21:27.481
[ Laughing ]

21:27.550 --> 21:30.205
[ Pedestrians Screaming ]

21:30.275 --> 21:32.067
[ Growling ]

21:32.136 --> 21:34.067
[ Sputtering ]

21:34.136 --> 21:37.517
WHO'S KICKING WHO AROUND NOW?

21:37.586 --> 21:38.862
[ Growling ]

21:38.931 --> 21:42.862
[ Howling ]

21:45.862 --> 21:47.723
KNOCK, KNOCK.

21:47.792 --> 21:50.103
[ Growling And Sputtering ]
